!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

mad /mæd/

(madder,maddest) 

1. ADJ If you say that someone is mad , you mean that they are very angry. 狂怒的 [非正式] 

例： You're just mad at me because I don't want to go. 因为我不想去，你就冲我发火。 

2. ADJ You use mad to describe people or things that you think are very foolish. 蠢疯的 [表不满] 

例： You'd be mad to work with him again. 你要是再和他一起工作就是蠢疯了。 

3. madness N-UNCOUNT 蠢疯 

例： It is political madness. 这是政治蠢疯。 

4. ADJ Someone who is mad has a mind that does not work in a normal way, with the result that their behaviour is very strange. (人) 疯的 

例： She was afraid of going mad. 她担心变疯。 

5. madness N-UNCOUNT 疯 

例： He was driven to the brink of madness. 他被逼到了疯狂的边缘。 

6. ADJ If you are mad about something or someone, you like them very much. 疯迷的 [非正式] [v-link ADJ 'about/on' n] 

例： She's not as mad about sports as I am. 她不像我那样对体育疯迷。 

例： He's mad about you. 他对你疯迷。 

7. COMB in ADJ Mad is also a combining form. 疯迷…的 (用于构成合成词) [英国英语] 

例： ...his football-mad son. …他的疯迷足球的儿子。 

8. ADJ Mad behaviour is wild and uncontrolled. (行为) 疯狂的 

例： You only have an hour to complete the game so it's a mad dash against the clock. 你们只有一个小时完成比赛，因此这是和时间的一次疯狂角逐。 

9. madly ADV 疯狂地 [ADV with v] 

例： Down in the streets people were waving madly. 下面大街上，人们在疯狂地挥手。 

10. PHRASE If you say that someone or something drives you mad , you mean that you find them extremely annoying. 使某人发疯 [非正式] 

例： There are certain things he does that drive me mad. 他干的某些事使我发疯。 

11. PHRASE If you do something like mad , you do it very energetically or enthusiastically. 疯了似地 [非正式] 

例： He was weight training like mad. 他在疯了似地进行举重训练。 

12.  →  see also madly

